# Supplier relationship policy

[Azure wiki page](https://dev.azure.com/medrecord/MEDrecord%20ISMS/_wiki/wikis/MEDrecord-ISMS.wiki/1190/Supplier-relationship-policy)

# Summary

This policy describes rules and principles on how we manage supplier relationships and how it is applied in our organization.

# Principles

INLINE
The contract should contain our requirements for information security:

Access to data and conditions;

Service level agreement;

Submission to relevant Policies;

If the supplier will process PII (personally identifiable information) on our behalf:

A data processing agreement (DPA, *verwerkersovereenkomst*) must be available;

The data should be located within the EU;

US cloud service providers should have a privacy policy in which they adhere to GDPR;

A selection of key suppliers should be assessed periodically on the following subjects:

General performance (price/quality considerations, disagreements, reasons for termination such as a serious incident);

SLA-compliance (Service Level Agreement) (are they living up to the expectations, on time, in time?);

Recent incidents (were they a party in a recent information security incident?);

Suppliers and relevant documents are to be added to our inventory;

Reasoning for including a supplier in the periodic evaluation reports should be provided;

A quarterly Supplier Evaluation Report is completed by management. Evaluation outcomes are documented and stored in the ISMS for review and audit purposes.

# Responsibilities

The Information security officer is responsible to keep this policy up to date

Management will approve all changes

The service manager and office manager are responsible to implement the policy

